==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|stif|stīf|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|stifaz}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|stīpos}} (compare {{etyl|la}} {{term|stipare}}, from which English {{term|stevedore}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/stɪf/}}
* {{audio|en-us-stiff.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɪf}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er}}

# Of an object, [[rigid]], hard to bend, [[inflexible]].
# {{context|figuratively}} Of policies and rules and their application and enforcement, inflexible.
# Of a person, [[formal]] in behavior, unrelaxed.
# {{colloquial}} [[harsh|Harsh]], [[severe]].
#: ''He was eventually caught, and given a '''stiff''' fine.''
# Of muscles, or parts of the body, [[painful]], as a result of excessive, or [[unaccustomed]] exercise.
#: ''My legs are '''stiff''' after climbing that hill yesterday.''
# [[potent]].
#: ''A '''stiff''' drink; a '''stiff''' dose; a '''stiff''' breeze.''
# [[dead]], [[deceased]]
# {{rfd-redundant}} Of a [[penis]], [[erect]]

